article.linkText: Perry scores 30 as Loyola (MD) knocks off Army 71-65
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- — Deon Perry's 30 points led Loyola (MD) over Army 71-65 on Wednesday night. Perry shot 8 for 14 (3 for 4 from 3-point range) and 11 of 12 from the free throw line for the Greyhounds (3-13, 1-2 Patriot League). D'Angelo Stines was 3 of 10 shooting (2 for 4 from 3-point range) to add 10 points. Golden Dike was 4 of 6 shooting and 1 of 4 from the free throw line to finish with nine points. Abe Johnson finished with 17 points and eight rebounds for the Black Knights (5-11, 1-2). Army also got 15 points and two steals from TJ Small. In addition, Blake Barker finished with nine points. Both teams next play Saturday. Loyola (MD) hosts Boston University and Army goes on the road to play American. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
